        <div n="432A800Z" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-432A800Z-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-432A800Z-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-432A800Z-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1">Sept<hi rend="sup">br</hi> 08. 7<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 08. 1728.</l></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-432A800Z-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-432A800Z-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-432A800Z-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1">N<hi rend="sup">r</hi> 08. 4</l></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-432A800Z-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-432A800Z-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-432A800Z-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-432A800Z-line-1">A slave to cro<unclear>w overu</unclear>ds, scortch't with the summers heats,</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-432A800Z-line-2"> In Court the wretched Lawyer toyls and sweats</l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-432A800Z-line-3"> While smiling Nature in her best attire</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-432A800Z-line-4"> Does sooth each sense and vernal joy inspire.</l><l n="5" xml:id="spp-432A800Z-line-5"> Can he, who knows that real good should please</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-432A800Z-line-6"> Barter for gold his Liberty and Ease?Thus Paulus preach'd: When entring at the door</l><l n="7" xml:id="spp-432A800Z-line-7"> Upon his board a Clyent pours the ore:</l><l n="8" xml:id="spp-432A800Z-line-8"> He grasps the shining gift, pores o'er the Cause,</l><l n="9" xml:id="spp-432A800Z-line-9"> Forgets the S<unclear>u overa</unclear>n, and dozes on the Laws.432A800Z   </l></lg></div>
